    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Small to medium, dark-red species, often with patches of iridescent green, blue and yellow. Erect axes emerge from an extensive holdfast and some of these curve to the sides and are secondarily attached to the substratum by small pads. Vertical axes formed of a series of bulging bead-like segments that are each longer than broad. At the joints short lateral branches emerge, often arranged in whorls around main axis.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7619",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Two forms see. Iridescent clumps typically only about 20 mm tall, but pale brown ones as large as 200 mm. Axes about 2 mm wide.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7620",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> South Africa endemic.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u><i> </i>West coast though to about Port St. Johns.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7621",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Common in algal turfs from low intertidal and shallow reefs, especially in pools. Iridescent plants are easy to spot, but many of larger ones are plain brown and recognised by their beaded structure.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7622",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7623",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Spore-producing structures (sporangia) found in central cavities of axes; spherical and about 0.1 mm in diameter, each divided into 8 spores.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7624",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Can be confused with the Compressed champia <i>C. compressa,</i> which is also dark reddish-brown, has similar habits and distribution and is also iridescent, but that species has flattened rather than cylindrical axes.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7625",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Further reading / References",
